# Debenture Definition

> ## Excerpt
> A debenture is a type of [[Debt|debt]] — issued by governments and corporations — that lacks [[Collateral|collateral]], and is therefore dependent on the [[Creditworthiness|creditworthiness]] and reputation of the issuer.

